<body>

    <h1>Cloudflare + GitHub Pages SSL Setup</h1>

    <h2>Phase 1: Cloudflare Encryption</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Log into your <strong>Cloudflare Dashboard</strong>.</li>
        <li>Select <code>rocksdesign.ca</code>.</li>
        <li>Open <strong>SSL/TLS</strong> from the sidebar.</li>
        <li>Set encryption mode to <strong>Full</strong> or <strong>Full (Strict)</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Phase 2: Bypass Proxies</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Go to <strong>DNS ➔ Records</strong> in Cloudflare.</li>
        <li>Locate your <strong>A records</strong> and <code>www</code> <strong>CNAME</strong>.</li>
        <li>Change status from <strong>Proxied (Orange)</strong> to <strong>DNS Only (Grey)</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Phase 3: GitHub Activation</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Open GitHub repository <code>Atlanfa/InterOS</code>.</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>Settings ➔ Pages</strong>.</li>
        <li>Remove <code>rocksdesign.ca</code>, click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
        <li>Re-enter <code>rocksdesign.ca</code>, click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
        <li>Check the <strong>Enforce HTTPS</strong> box once verified.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Phase 4: Restore CDN</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Return to Cloudflare <strong>DNS ➔ Records</strong>.</li>
        <li>Switch records back to <strong>Proxied (Orange)</strong>.</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>SSL/TLS ➔ Edge Certificates</strong>.</li>
        <li>Enable <strong>Always Use HTTPS</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="footer">
        InterOS Deployment Guide • Deployment Verified
    </div>

